<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 16 at 5:38PM MDT  by NWS Billings</headline>
<description>...Thunderstorms will impact portions of central Yellowstone County
through 615 PM MDT...
At 536 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a pair of thunderstorms
near Huntley, or 16 miles northeast of Billings, moving east at 10
mph.
HAZARD...Pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects and vegetation is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Shepherd, Huntley, Worden and Ballantine. Motorists on I-94 near
Worden.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
